{
  "texts": [
    "The controllable design of TrafficVLM can be strengthened by using a text encoder to impose different conditions on the description generation.Figure 1.1Figure1.",
    "Overview of our method.",
    "First the sub-global and local frame sequences are extracted from the vehicle camera video.",
    "Some local frames might be missing, depending on the availability of the bounding boxes in the event segment.",
    "A visual feature extractor fe is then applied to both of them to get the two visual embeddings x g and parts of x l. The sub-global embedding is trimmed to the event segment and subsampled to create the sub-global feature xg."
  ]
}